column1: Notes: Where councils have provided a figure of fewer than five, BBC News has adjusted this to <5 in order to prevent the risk of identification. Larger numbers in breakdowns have also been recorded as "Anonymised" if there is a possibility that numbers under five could be calculated.
Where <5 children from one country were all within one council area, we have removed the figure from the individual local authority's data to prevent identification
Individual figures may therefore not add up to the totals provided.

This sheet also includes nationalities of "care leavers", formerly children in care now aged 18 or over, whose details were also supplied by some councils in response to the FOI request, but who could not be removed from the analysis.
